You are implementing the audit API routes (`app/api/pipeline/audit/run/route.ts` and supporting routes) for a video production pipeline editor. These endpoints launch parallel Claude Code agents that render Remotion stills and compare frames against specs for each section.

Requirements
1. `POST /api/pipeline/audit/run` — accepts `{ sections?: string[] }` (defaults to all). Launches one agent per section concurrently. Returns SSE stream with `{ jobId }`.
2. Each per-section agent: calls `renderStill()` for segment midpoints → calls `runClaudeAnalysis()` comparing the still PNG against the spec file → writes `specs/{sectionId}/AUDIT_{specName}.md` with pass/fail verdict and details.
3. `GET /api/pipeline/audit/results` — returns `{ sections: AuditSectionResult[] }` where `AuditSectionResult = { sectionId: string; passCount: number; failCount: number; status: 'done' | 'pending' | 'error'; specs: SpecAuditResult[] }` and `SpecAuditResult = { specFile: string; verdict: 'pass' | 'fail'; summary: string; frameFile?: string }`.
4. No authentication required.

