Prompt Dependencies:
- types_TypeScript.prompt — provides `PipelineStage`, `AnnotationAnalysis`
- lib_jobs_TypeScript.prompt — provides `runPipelineStage`, `registerExecutor`
- lib_claude_TypeScript.prompt — provides `runClaudeAnalysis`
- lib_render_TypeScript.prompt — provides `renderStill`
- lib_project_TypeScript.prompt — provides `loadProject`

Instructions
- Still output path: `outputs/audit/{sectionId}/{specName}_frame.png`.
- Audit report path: `specs/{sectionId}/AUDIT_{specName}.md`.
- Claude analysis prompt: read the still PNG file and the spec file, return `AnnotationAnalysis` JSON with verdict.
- Concurrent agents: `await Promise.all(sections.map(sectionId => auditSection(sectionId, send, onLog)))`.
- Emit per-section events: `{ type: 'audit-section', sectionId, status: 'running' | 'done' | 'error', passCount, failCount }`.
- `GET /api/pipeline/audit/results`: parse AUDIT_*.md files to extract verdicts (parse the `## Verdict` heading).
- Register executor: `registerExecutor('audit', ...)`.

Deliverable
- `app/api/pipeline/audit/run/route.ts` — POST endpoint for parallel section auditing.
- `app/api/pipeline/audit/results/route.ts` — GET endpoint for audit results.

Implementation assumptions (explicit)
- Audit MARKDOWN files have a structured format: `## Verdict\n{pass|fail}\n## Summary\n{text}`.
- Multiple stills per section correspond to spec file count (one still per spec segment).

Please produce production-ready prompt content that will generate the module consistent with the above.
